@startuml
title HelloUpscaler Architecture and FSDK Relationship

skinparam monochrome true
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam defaultTextAlignment left

package "Application Layer" {
  class "HelloUpscaler sample" as Sample {
    +wWinMain()
    +WindowProc()
    +RecreateTargets()
    +EnsureFsrContext()
    +UpdateJitter()
    +DispatchUpscaler()
  }

  class "AppState" as AppState {
    +deviceManager
    +imguiRenderer
    +scenePipeline
    +presentPipeline
    +targets
    +fsr
    +ui state
  }

  class "OffscreenTargets" as Targets {
    +sceneColor
    +sceneDepth
    +motionVectors
    +upscaledOutput
    +renderWidth/renderHeight
    +displayWidth/displayHeight
  }

  class "FsrState" as FsrState {
    +ffx::Context
    +contextFlags
    +maxRenderSize
    +maxUpscaleSize
    +jitterPhaseCount
    +estimatedMemoryUsageMb
  }
}

package "LightD3D12 Layer" {
  class "DeviceManager" as DeviceManager
  class "RenderDevice" as RenderDevice {
    +CreateTexture()
    +Destroy()
    +CreateRenderPipeline()
    +GetNativeDevice()
    +GetNativeTextureResource()
  }
  class "ICommandBuffer" as CommandBuffer {
    +CmdBeginRendering()
    +CmdEndRendering()
    +CmdTransitionTexture()
    +GetNativeGraphicsCommandList()
  }
  class "ImguiRenderer" as ImguiRenderer
}

package "AMD FSDK Layer" {
  class "ffx::Query" as FfxQuery
  class "ffx::CreateContext" as FfxCreate
  class "ffx::DispatchDescUpscale" as FfxDispatch
  class "ffx::Context" as FfxContext
  class "DX12 bridge" as FfxDx12 {
    +ffxApiGetResourceDX12(...)
  }
}

package "GPU Resources" {
  artifact "sceneColor\nRTV + SRV" as SceneColor
  artifact "motionVectors\nRTV + SRV" as MotionVectors
  artifact "sceneDepth\nDSV + SRV" as SceneDepth
  artifact "upscaledOutput\nUAV + SRV" as UpscaledOutput
  artifact "swapchain backbuffer\nRTV" as Backbuffer
}

Sample --> AppState : owns
AppState --> Targets : owns
AppState --> FsrState : owns
AppState --> DeviceManager : owns
AppState --> ImguiRenderer : owns

DeviceManager --> RenderDevice : provides
Sample --> RenderDevice : uses through DeviceManager
Sample --> CommandBuffer : records frame work

RenderDevice --> SceneColor : creates
RenderDevice --> MotionVectors : creates
RenderDevice --> SceneDepth : creates
RenderDevice --> UpscaledOutput : creates

Sample --> FfxQuery : asks for render resolution\nand jitter info
Sample --> FfxCreate : creates/destroys context
FfxCreate --> FfxContext : initializes
FsrState --> FfxContext : stores

Sample --> FfxDx12 : wraps native textures/lists
RenderDevice --> FfxDx12 : exposes native device/resource
CommandBuffer --> FfxDx12 : exposes native command list

Sample --> FfxDispatch : fills dispatch inputs
FfxDispatch --> SceneColor : reads
FfxDispatch --> MotionVectors : reads
FfxDispatch --> SceneDepth : reads
FfxDispatch --> UpscaledOutput : writes

Sample --> Backbuffer : presents final image
ImguiRenderer --> Backbuffer : overlays UI

note right of Sample
The sample is the coordinator.
It does not implement the upscale algorithm itself.
It prepares resources, gathers camera/frame data,
and hands everything to AMD FSDK.
end note

note bottom of Targets
Logical outputs of the scene pass:
- sceneColor
- motionVectors
- sceneDepth

Logical output of the FSR pass:
- upscaledOutput
end note

note right of FfxDispatch
This is where the relationship with FSDK becomes real.
The sample converts LightD3D12 resources into DX12 handles,
fills the FSR dispatch structure,
and the SDK executes the temporal upscale pass.
end note

note bottom of Backbuffer
The swapchain backbuffer is not an FSR input.
It only receives the final present pass result:
- sceneColor directly if FSR is disabled
- upscaledOutput if FSR is enabled
end note

newpage
title Frame Flow

start

:Begin frame;
:Handle window messages and ImGui state;
:Query display size;

if (FSR enabled?) then (yes)
  :Query desired internal resolution\nfrom quality mode;
else (no)
  :Use display resolution as internal resolution;
endif

:Recreate targets if resolution changed;
:Ensure FSR context exists and matches sizes;
:Query jitter and update projection;

:Scene pass;
note right
Writes:
- sceneColor
- motionVectors
- sceneDepth
end note

if (FSR enabled?) then (yes)
  :Transition inputs/outputs to FSR states;
  :Build ffx::DispatchDescUpscale;
  :Dispatch AMD FSR;
  note right
Inputs:
- sceneColor
- motionVectors
- sceneDepth
- frame timing
- camera parameters
- reset flag

Output:
- upscaledOutput
end note
else (no)
  :Skip FSR dispatch;
endif

:Present pass;
note right
If FSR is disabled:
- sample sceneColor

If FSR is enabled:
- sample upscaledOutput
end note

:ImGui pass overlays UI on backbuffer;
:Submit command buffer and present swapchain;
stop

@enduml
